	<p class="cs4B09651A"><div style="width:49pt;height:32pt;border-width:0.5pt;border-style:solid;border-color:Black;background-color:#FFFFFF;margin:0pt 9pt 0pt 9pt;padding:5pt 0pt 0pt 0pt;">
		<p class="csD4EB832D"><span class="cs6D9F0C8B">FISCAL NOTE</span></p></div>
	<span class="cs9C2C975F">WEST VIRGINIA LEGISLATURE</span></p><p class="csDC685BE1"><span class="cs3BC7FF6A">2025 </span><span class="csA79677C3">REGULAR SESSION</span></p><p class="cs4B09651A"><span class="csA79677C3">Introduced</span></p><p class="csF36D445B"><span class="cs9C2C975F">House Bill 3255</span></p><p class="csCA3E41D9"><span class="csBB3ABC40">By Delegates Hornbuckle, Young, Fluharty, Lewis, Garcia, Hamilton, Williams, Hansen, and Pushkin</span></p><p class="csBA891411"><span class="csA9049697">[Introduced March 07, 2025; referred to the Committee on Health and Human Resources then Finance]</span></p><p class="cs488BC2"><span class="csE736517A">A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding thereto a new article designated &sect;7-28-1, &sect;7-28-2, &sect;7-28-3, &sect;7-28-4, &sect;7-28-5, &sect;7-28-6 and &sect;7-28-7, relating to authorizing counties to establish a county daycare; providing for a petition process to instigate the creation of a county daycare; allowing a county commission to propose a fee, tax or levy to pay for creating and maintaining the county daycare; allowing a county commission to establish a county daycare authority; providing for a county vote on creating and funding a daycare; to establish and manage a county daycare; and allowing a county commission to fund or alternatively propose a tax, fee, or levy to fund the daycare for voter approval; and providing guidelines for establishing and managing the daycare.</span></p><p class="cs55F91DED"><span class="cs50A3B802">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs55F91DED"><span class="cs50A3B802">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs317696C1">ARTICLE 25. ESTABLISHMENT OF A COUNTY DAYCARE.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs5BCBAEC9">&sect;7-28-1. Establishment of a County Daycare.</span></h4>
	<p class="csCF6B950C"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="csCF6B950C"><span class="csF2E808A1">Upon the passage of a county referendum, each county commission is hereby authorized to establish a public agency to be known as the &quot;County Daycare Authority&quot; to carry out the powers and duties herein conferred by law upon the county relating to establishment and management of available and affordable daycare for all citizens of the county.</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs5BCBAEC9">&sect;7-28-2. Establishment of a County Daycare Authority; authorization to assess a local levy, tax, or fee; and determining cost of operation and maintenance.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(a) </span><span class="cs13A1C9D2">Legislative finding and authorization to create a county daycare</span><span class="csF2E808A1">- The Legislature finds that the establishment of county run daycare is in the public interest, a component of economic development, provides educational enhancement to the children of the county, promotes workforce availability of parents, and is a public service that improves the quality of life of the residents of a county. &nbsp;Therefore, each county may establish a county daycare pursuant to this section. &nbsp;The county daycare shall be for the benefit of the citizens of the county. &nbsp;If two or more adjourning counties meet the requirements of this article, they may enter a memorandum of understanding and combine resources to create a joint daycare authority upon adoption of referendums by each county.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(1) </span><span class="cs13A1C9D2">Petition by the citizens</span><span class="csF2E808A1">- County resident voters may petition the county commission to establish a county daycare. The county commission, shall upon receipt and verification of a petition received signed in their own handwriting by at least 10% of the registered voters of the county voting in the last gubernatorial election, as verified by the county clerk, make a petition for the imposition of a levy, tax, or fee for the purpose of creating and maintaining within the county a daycare facility for use by citizens of the county, shall be submitted to the voters in a county-wide referendum at the next general election held in the county. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(2) </span><span class="cs13A1C9D2">County Commission initiative</span><span class="csF2E808A1">- A county commission may initiate a referendum to decide the issue of establishment of a county daycare. </span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(3) </span><span class="cs13A1C9D2">County Commission to develop daycare proposal</span><span class="csF2E808A1">- Prior to a county commission presenting the question to the voters of the establishment of a county daycare, it shall fulfill the requirements of &sect;7-25-3 of this code providing a description of the design and methodology for funding the county daycare, all to be included and reasonably described in the ballot measure presented to voters. </span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(b) </span><span class="cs13A1C9D2">Assessment of a tax, fee, or levy</span><span class="csF2E808A1">- Upon enactment by majority vote by referendum, a county may establish a county daycare authority for the purpose of establishing and managing a county daycare and fund its creation an operation by the funding source. &nbsp;Each county commission so authorized to assess a tax, levy, or fee, upon directive by passage of ballot initiative in the county is hereby authorized to initiate such tax, levy, or fee to be utilized for the purpose of construction and operation of a county daycare facility or facilities:</span><span class="cs13A1C9D2"> Provided, </span><span class="csF2E808A1">That notwithstanding the provisions of this article to the contrary, if a county commission can fund the creation and management of a county daycare without the assessment of any fee, tax, or levy, the county commission may establish a daycare authority and authorize a daycare by its own initiative without any requirement to present the issue by referendum to the voters.</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs5BCBAEC9">&sect;7-28-3. Petition for a county daycare.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(a) Referendums shall be held in conjunction with a general election which the requirements of this article relating to planning and determining the levy amount have been met and allows the referendum to meet all election notice and filing deadlines.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(b) The county commission shall, if the petition directs the assessment of the levy, tax, or fee for creation of a daycare authority, provide an analysis of the amount that the fee, tax, or levy must generate to pay for the county daycare operations and to the extent practical, the average cost to individual taxpayers. &nbsp;If the petition fails to provide a funding mechanism, and the county commission determines the county does not have adequate funds to establish a daycare, the county commission shall determine what levy, tax, or fee is best to be used for this purpose. If a levy is selected as the funding source, the levy shall be initiated pursuant to the provisions of &sect;11-8-6b of the code. &nbsp;If the petition for creating of a county daycare does specify how the funding of the daycare shall occur, and if the fee, tax, or levy in the county commission&rsquo;s judgement will not adequately fund a daycare facility, the commission may alter the ballot question to presented to voters to assure it will be sufficiently funded, then the county commission shall select any funding method and include that language in the county referendum.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(c) &nbsp;Upon a vote of a county commission to establish a county daycare or the receipt of a verified petition, the county commission shall undertake a study to determine the most economical and timely plans to establish a county daycare facility or facilities sufficient to meet the needs of county residents. &nbsp;The county commission shall determine the proposed levy rate assessment on real property or the assessment of a county tax or fee to cover the cost of establishing and maintaining a daycare facility or facilities, including sufficient monies needed to provide daycare services at an affordable rate for residents based on the ability to pay of residents needing the service. Upon completion of the plan, the county commission shall cause a public hearing and receive public comment on the proposal, providing a Class I notice published in the county 10 days prior to the hearing. &nbsp;After receipt of public comment, the county commission may revise the plan but if the county commission revises the plan and the cost will vary more or less than 10% of the original estimate, the commission shall conduct another hearing and receive comment on the new plan. </span></p><h4 class="cs5AD36D8A">
		<span class="cs5BCBAEC9">&sect;7-28-4. County daycare levy placed upon ballot; notices; form of ballot.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(a) Upon receipt of a valid petition pursuant to &sect;7-28-2 of this code, and the development of a plan, the county commission shall publish a notice, announcing the levy being on the ballot at the next scheduled election, as a Class II-0 legal advertisement in compliance with the provisions of &sect;59-3-1 </span><span class="cs13A1C9D2">et seq</span><span class="csF2E808A1">. of this code, and the publication area for such publication shall be the county. Such notice shall be so published within 14 consecutive days next preceding the election. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(b) The question on the special levy shall be placed on the ballot in accordance with the ballot placement order prescribed by &sect;3-5-13a(a) of this code. The question heading shall be entitled: &quot;Special Levy Election&quot; and the question shall be significantly in the following form: &quot;Special election to authorize an ____ (a levy, fee, or tax) for the year(s) ____________ and for the purpose of establishing/continuing a county daycare.&quot;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(c) The additional levy, tax, or fee shall be collected from __________________ (describe the type of tax, levy, or fee and how and from whom it will be collected.)</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(d) In the event that a majority of the votes cast upon a question submitted pursuant to this section at any election be against the question, the question may again be submitted to the voters at the next succeeding election.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs5BCBAEC9">&sect;7-28-5. Management and oversight vested in authority; appointment and terms of members; vacancies; removal of members; meetings; quorum; compensation.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(a) Upon approval of the voters of a county daycare proposal, the county of this state is hereby authorized to establish a public agency to be known as the &quot;County Daycare Authority&quot; to carry out the powers and duties conferred by this article relating to establishment and management of available and affordable daycare for all citizens of the county. &nbsp;The management and control of the authority, its property, operations, business and affairs shall be lodged in an authority of five persons who shall be known as &quot;members of the authority,&quot; each of whom shall be appointed by the county commission for a term of three years, except that as to the first seven appointed to the first authority appointed, the term of two members shall expire on July 1, next ensuing, the terms of the next two members shall expire on July 1, two years thereafter, and the term of three members shall expire on July 1, three years thereafter. Each member shall hold office until the expiration of the term for which such member is appointed or until a successor shall have been duly appointed and shall have qualified. Vacancies on the authority shall be filled by appointment of the county commission for the unexpired term of the member whose office shall be vacant. One member shall be a member of the county commission or the commission&rsquo;s designee, two members shall be parents of children that will in the future, currently or in the past had children attending the county daycare; one member shall be an expert in finance and budgeting; and one member who has expertise in child development or education.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(b) Each of the authority members shall be reimbursed for all reasonable and necessary expenses actually incurred in the performance of the member&#39;s duties as a member of the authority, and receive per diem pay the same as received as members of the legislature pursuant to &sect;4-2A-1 </span><span class="cs13A1C9D2">et seq</span><span class="csF2E808A1">. of this code. All such compensation and expenses incurred by authority members shall be payable solely from funds of the authority.</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs5BCBAEC9">&sect;7-28-6. Authority to be a public corporation; name; power to contract and sue; seal.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">The authority and the members thereof, shall constitute and be a public corporation and as such shall have perpetual succession until discontinued by expiration or non-renewal of levy, tax, or fee, may contract and be contracted with, sue and be sued, plead and be impleaded and have and use a common seal.</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs5BCBAEC9">&sect;7-28-7. Powers, duties and responsibilities of authority generally.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">The authority may exercise all powers necessary or appropriate to carry out and effectuate its corporate purpose. The authority may:</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(1) Adopt, and from time to time, amend and repeal bylaws necessary and proper for the regulation of its affairs and the conduct of its business and rules and regulations to implement and make effective its powers and duties.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(2) Acquire, construct, enlarge, improve, furnish, equip, maintain, repair, operate, lease or rent to, or contract for operation by a governmental agency or person, one or more facilities, and adopt rules and regulations for operation of these facilities.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(3) Acquire by gift or purchase, hold and dispose of real and personal property in the exercise of its powers and the performance of its duties.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(4) Make and enter into all contracts and agreements and execute all instruments necessary or incidental to the performance of its duties and the execution of its powers.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(5) Employ an executive director and authorize the hiring of other employees, and retain or contract with consulting engineers, financial consultants, accounting experts, architects, attorneys and such other consultants and independent contractors as are necessary in its judgment to carry out the provisions of this article and fix the compensation or fees thereof.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(6) Receive and accept from any federal or state agency grants for or in aid of the construction and operation of any daycare facility or and receive and accept aid or contributions from any source of money, property, labor or other things of value, to be held, used and applied only for the purposes for which such grants and contributions are made.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(7) Purchase insurance protecting the authority and its officers and employees to protect authority assets and protect lawful actions undertaken by the authority and its employees fulfilling their lawful duties.</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(8) Establish fees for daycare services that are scaled on the child or children&rsquo;s parents or guardians&rsquo; ability to pay. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csF2E808A1">(9) Do all acts necessary and proper to carry out the powers expressly granted to the authority by this article.</span></p><p class="csDE8452F9"><span class="csAD690475">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="csDE8452F9"><span class="csAD690475">NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to allow for the creation of a county daycare by any county commission, allowing a petition process to cause an election relating to the establishment of a county daycare; &nbsp;requiring a county commission, when petitioned by voters or by its own directive, develop a plan for the daycare and propose a fee, tax, or levy to pay for it; &nbsp;allowing counties to establish a county daycare authority to manage the operation; and granting a county daycare general authority to do what is necessary to establish and manage a daycare.</span></p><p class="csDE8452F9"><span class="csAD690475">Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added.</span></p>


</div>
 
 
